A vintage-style illustration of a wooden craftsman's workbench viewed from above, where an artisan's hands are carefully disassembling a complex nested Russian matryoshka doll made of polished brass and copper gears. The opened dolls reveal smaller mechanical components inside, each layer containing intricate clockwork parts that are being methodically laid out flat across the worn oak surface. Warm afternoon light streams through a dusty workshop window, casting long shadows across scattered precision tools, calipers, and small brass plates arranged in neat rows. The aesthetic evokes 1920s technical illustration with muted sepia tones, crosshatching details, and the satisfying organization of complex nested objects being systematically unpacked and catalogued.
